Demon Lookup.Name: Lurgo (Legba)

Hyperstitial Interplay.Clicks: Gt-00, Lurgo is known as the First Door and the Door of Doors in Muvian sorcery. Her mesh number (00) clicks the 0th Gate (Gt-00), linking her to a highly occulted region in numogrammatic cartography.

Demon Lookup.Title: Amphidemon of Openings (The Door of Doors)
Rite Details: Her major rite is detailed as a path requiring repeated patience, subtlety, and compliance.
Described as a numogrammatic 'plunge line' passing through the 8th gate (Gt-36).
It maps to yogic practices of spinal descent and is evoked in various contemporary myths and dream sorcery practices.

Demonic Associations.Associations: Lurgo is mentioned as 'nesting' these demons. This nesting relationship is significant in the context of the Munumese saying 'the end lies within the beginning'. Lurgo is also said to dwell between Murrumur & Uttunul, beneath the sea but above the twins in the furnace.
Demonic Associations.Name: Minommo
Murrumur
Demonic Associations.Additional Note: Additionally, the 'plunge line' of Lurgo's rite passes through the lair of Murrumur.

Demonic Associations.Name: Uttunul
Demonic Associations.Additional Note: Lurgo's rite also descends following a numogrammatic line that passes through the lair of Uttunul.

Symbolic and Esoteric Associations: In Tzikvik tradition, she is called Oogvhu, the Immortal Worm of primordial communication.
In Haitian Voodoo, she is paralleled by Legba, the first and last of the Loa to be invoked in rituals.
In Western esotericism, particularly in the context of the Decadence game, Lurgo is unique for allowing a termination without loss.
She is connected to the golem myth in esoteric Judaism and to the concept of the Original Subtraction.
Lurgo's domain is positioned between the orbits of Mercury and the Sun in Lemurian Planetworks.
Lurgo is described as having a pitch of Ana-1 and is noted for her absence of imps, attributed to her primordiality or ultimateness.
Her name in the Old Muvian Tongue is Gl’eiaoung, translated as 'The Initiator' in Munumese and English.
Her net-span is linked to the concept of binary code and Taoist polarities of Yang and Yin.
The I Ching's code of unbroken and broken lines is suggested to be a relic of a primordial language first enunciated by Lurgo.
Horowitz's research into the 'gl' subphoneme of Lurgo's name suggests its significance to the glottopolitics of the English language, leading to a labyrinth of 'glitter-glyphs'.
Lurgo is noted for concluding each Decadence Aeon without loss, and is key in the Decadology system of the Western uptake of Pandemonium.

Demon Lookup.Name: Duoddod
Demon Lookup.Title: Amphidemon of Abstract Addiction

Rites (Rt).Description: [27541890] Datacomb searches digital exactitude (every second counts)

Rite Details: The pineal-regression rite emphasizes a deep dive into subconscious and esoteric knowledge, possibly linking to ancient mystical traditions and occult practices.
The datacomb searches rite alludes to a meticulous and obsessive quest for precision and exactitude, resonullt with modern digital data analysis and information processing.

Demonic Associations.Name: Doogu
Demonic Associations.Additional Note: The syzygetic relationship with Doogu (Mesh-02) emphasizes the dualistic nature of Duoddod, embodying the tension between division and unity.

Symbolic and Esoteric Associations: Embodies the essence of duplicity, mirroring, and the abstract nature of addiction in both a metaphorical and literal sense.
Identified in Muvian sorcery with the Second Door, invoked as the 'Main Lo-Way' into the Crypt by K-goth cults.
Described by Horovitz as 'reduplicating its double-twinness though its multitude' in relation to Zone-2, reflecting its complex and reflexive nature.

Demon Lookup.Name: Doogu (The Blob)
Demon Lookup.Title: Cyclic Chronodemon of Splitting-Waters

Rites (Rt).Description: [27541] Mj. Slow pull to stasis ~ protection from drowning

Rite Details: Doogu's rites are deeply entwined with primordial and elemental forces, emphasizing themes of origin, division, and preservation.

Demonic Associations.Associations: Syzygetic relationship with Duoddod, highlighting themes of division and duality.
Demonic Associations.Name: Duoddod
Demonic Associations.Additional Note: Together, Doogu and Duoddod form a complex interplay between splitting and duplicity within Phase 2 of the Numogram.

Symbolic and Esoteric Associations: Represents the primordial division of the original unity, echoing mythological themes of creation through splitting or separation.
Associated with elemental forces of water and earth, symbolizing the dynamic interplay between fluidity and solidity, change and stability.
